  <prompt>
    Author `PromoteToMatterMemoryHandler` (NEW) at `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Handlers/PromoteToMatterMemoryHandler.cs` implementing the T2 ‚Üí T3 `promote_to_matter_memory({fact, source, approvalRequired})` tool per architecture ¬ß6.4 + ¬ß8.1. CRITICAL: this handler does NOT auto-write to T3 ‚Äî it QUEUES a pending-approval record (Cosmos `memory` container, doc-type `matter-memory-promotion`) via `MatterMemoryPromotionService` (task 093) and returns `{ factId, status: "pending_approval" | "written" | "rejected" }`. When `approvalRequired: true` the status is always `pending_approval` and the actual T3 write happens later via the `/api/memory/promotions/{id}/approve` endpoint (task 094). Implements FR-30 + FR-32 (promotion workflow surface).
  </prompt>

  <role>SPAARKE platform BFF developer. Expert in chat tool-handler authoring + T2 ‚Üí T3 promotion boundaries.</role>

  <goal>
    `PromoteToMatterMemoryHandler` lives at `Services/Ai/Handlers/PromoteToMatterMemoryHandler.cs` implementing `IToolHandler`. Delegates to `IMatterMemoryPromotionService.QueueForApprovalAsync` (task 093) ‚Äî does NOT call `MatterMemoryService.AppendFactAsync` directly. Validates: matter context present (else `{ status: "rejected", reason: "no_matter_context" }`); `fact ‚â§500 chars`; `source` non-empty. Returns `{ factId, status }` per ¬ß8.1. Single `ToolResult`. Tier-1-safe telemetry (no fact text). Unit tests cover pending_approval happy path, no_matter_context rejection, validation failures.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per architecture ¬ß3.2 rule 2 (T2 ‚Üí T3 promotion is EXPLICIT) + ¬ß6.4 (promote-to-matter flow diagram) + ¬ß8.1 (promote_to_matter_memory schema). The handler is a thin queueing surface ‚Äî the actual T3 durable write happens only after user accept at the approval endpoint (task 094). This is a load-bearing privacy invariant per architecture ¬ß2 P6 (privacy by default ‚Äî T2 never auto-promotes to T3).
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Memory/MatterMemoryService.cs</file>
